The info on Motion Burst Read in datasheet is incomplete.
After Step 3 the Motion_Burst register needs to be addressed for reading prior to burst reading (up to) 14 bytes.

Example for TI's Delfino
void burst_XY(void){
	int ptr;
	CS_low();
	SpiaRegs.SPITXBUF = REG_Motion_Burst;
	SpiaRegs.SPITXBUF = 0x50;
	DELAY_US(tSWW);
	SpiaRegs.SPITXBUF = REG_Motion_Burst;
	DELAY_US(tSRAD);
	for (ptr=0; ptr<14; ptr++){
		SpiaRegs.SPIDAT = (0x00);
		IDLE();
		burstXY[ptr]=SPI_RTRN;
	}
	CS_high();
}
SPI ISR returns SPI_RTRN
